Integrated Indigo Limited, a public relations firm, has emerged as the best PR/communications agency promoting sustainability at the 2021 edition of the Social Enterprise and Responsibility Awards, better known as The SERAS CSR Awards. The SERAS is said to be Africa’s first and foremost recognition or accolade for corporate social responsibility and sustainability. At the award ceremony held recently in Lagos, the organisers said Indigo won the award due to its vast contribution and role in promoting the activities of its clients in different areas of sustainability. Indigo wins SERAS award In his keynote speech, Ken Egbas, founder of SERAS, stated that the award was well-deserved, considering the passion and commitment of the agency in promoting excellence through several sustainability initiatives embarked upon by its clients. He added that the recognition should serve as a constant reminder for the recipient to continue to do more in impacting society. Speaking shortly after receiving the award, Bolaji Abimbola, managing director of Integrated Indigo Limited, described the award as a testament to the immense capacity of the agency to deliver exceptional services for its clients on sustainability-related issues. While expressing profound appreciation to the award’s organiser on the recognition, Abimbola dedicated the award to the team and the clients who created the enabling environment for the agency to collaborate and thrive. “I am highly delighted to receive this award on behalf of the team. As an agency, we are grateful for the confidence reposed in delivering value to our esteemed clients,” she said. “This recognition means a lot to us and would further motivate us to do more in promoting our clients in a way that would make their businesses profitable and ensure that society is impacted positively through sustainability.”